To install Code Claude (Anthropic’s Claude integration for coding) on a Linux machine in an enterprise environment, the steps depend on how your company provides it.

There are typically 3 enterprise distribution models:

⸻

✅ 1️⃣ If Your Company Provides Claude via VS Code Extension (Most Common)

Claude is often provided through:
	•	Anthropic Claude
	•	Visual Studio Code (VS Code)
	•	Enterprise SSO login

🔹 Step 1 – Install VS Code (if not installed)

Ubuntu/Debian:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install wget gpg
wget -qO- https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc | gpg --dearmor > microsoft.gpg
sudo install -o root -g root -m 644 microsoft.gpg /usr/share/keyrings/
sudo sh -c 'echo "deb [arch=amd64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/microsoft.gpg] https://packages.microsoft.com/repos/code stable main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/vscode.list'
sudo apt update
sudo apt install code

RHEL/CentOS:

sudo rpm --import https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc
sudo sh -c 'echo -e "[code]\nname=Visual Studio Code\nbaseurl=https://packages.microsoft.com/yumrepos/vscode\nenabled=1\ngpgcheck=1\ngpgkey=https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc" > /etc/yum.repos.d/vscode.repo'
sudo dnf install code


⸻

🔹 Step 2 – Install Claude Extension
	1.	Open VS Code
	2.	Go to Extensions
	3.	Search for Claude
	4.	Install the enterprise-approved extension (often named Claude / Claude AI / Claude Code depending on org packaging)
	5.	Login using:
	•	SSO (Azure AD / Okta / Google Workspace)
	•	Enterprise API key

If your org uses private extension registry, they will provide:
	•	.vsix file
	•	Internal marketplace URL

To install from VSIX:

code --install-extension claude-enterprise.vsix


⸻

✅ 2️⃣ If Claude Is Provided as a CLI Tool (Enterprise API Access)

If your company provides API access to Claude via:
	•	Anthropic API
	•	Internal proxy gateway

🔹 Install via pip (if allowed)

pip install anthropic

Export your enterprise key:

export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="your-enterprise-key"

Test:

python
>>> import anthropic
>>> client = anthropic.Anthropic()
>>> client.messages.create(
... model="claude-3-opus-20240229",
... max_tokens=100,
... messages=[{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
... )


⸻

✅ 3️⃣ If Enterprise Uses Secure Proxy / Internal Portal

Some enterprises:
	•	Do NOT allow direct external API calls
	•	Route Claude through internal AI gateway
	•	Provide a containerized IDE

In that case you may need:

docker login registry.company.com
docker pull registry.company.com/claude-ide:latest
docker run -it registry.company.com/claude-ide:latest

OR access via:

https://ai.company.internal


⸻

🔐 Important Enterprise Checks

Before installing, verify:
	•	Do you need VPN?
	•	Is outbound traffic blocked?
	•	Is proxy required?

If behind proxy:

export HTTPS_PROXY=http://proxy.company.com:8080
export HTTP_PROXY=http://proxy.company.com:8080


⸻

🛠 Enterprise Troubleshooting

If login fails:
	•	Check SSO browser default
	•	Ensure system time is synced
	•	Verify firewall rules
	•	Confirm API key scope

